<ul><li>A block of metal of&nbsp;<b>known mass</b>&nbsp;in an&nbsp;<b>insulated container</b>.</li><li>An&nbsp;<b>electrical heater</b>&nbsp;inserted into a hole drilled in the metal is used to supply a&nbsp;<b>measured amount of electrical energy</b>.</li><li>A&nbsp;<b>thermometer</b>&nbsp;inserted into a second hole drilled into the metal is used to measure the <b>temperature rise</b>.</li><li>A small amount of&nbsp;<b>water</b>&nbsp;in the thermometer hole to&nbsp;<b>improve thermal contact</b>&nbsp;between the thermometer and the metal.&nbsp;</li></ul>